# Testing Maintenance

This repo now treats Jest + React Testing Library as part of the normal engineering baseline.

## Core Rules

- When changing code that already has unit coverage, keep those tests passing or update them to reflect the new intended behavior
- Do not rewrite, weaken, or delete tests just to force a green run
- When behavior changes intentionally, update assertions so the tests clearly describe the new requirement
- Prefer adding coverage for branching behavior, flow logic, and legacy/standalone mode differences when touching those areas

## Important Focus Areas

- `src/components/app/MemoriesPage/MemoriesPage.tsx`
- `src/components/app/QuizPage/QuizPage.tsx`
- `src/components/app/UploadPage.tsx`
- `src/components/app/LegacyFlowPage.tsx`
- route wrappers and mode-specific flow behavior in `src/App.tsx`

## Validation

- Run `npm run test` after touching tested behavior
- Keep the Husky pre-commit hook (`npm run lint && npm test`) working
